sentences: Jennifer J. Arroyo (born March 20, 1975 in Staten Island, New York) is an American bassist best known for her tenure in the Canadian heavy metal group Kittie.
Her career in Kittie started after Talena Atfield left Kittie in 2002 without citing any official reasons.
On March 23, 2005, Morgan Lander made a post indicating that both Marx and Arroyo had left the band.
In July 2012, Arroyo became a contestant on CBS's Big Brother 14.
She also runs her own production company, Jenncity Productions in New York City and was featured in the May 2007 issue of Revolver magazine.
Jennifer had previously befriended the band when she was with Spine while filming a performance on the short-lived television show Farmclub.com, in Los Angeles, California.
After 67 days, she was evicted from the house, placing fifth in the competition.
